  <bioghist id="aspace_e7d2d17a5c8e4399821183222e717f74">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Cornell University LL.B 1888. Edwin Hamlin was Dean of the Cornell Law School from 1916-1921, and taught there until 1927.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_c30cfe7f81b4c6d712d22673499009b0">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, certificates, and a small scrapbook of newspaper clippings and handwritten quotations. Letters are primarily from associates at Stanford University and students from Cornell University; correspondents include Morris Bishop, George Gleason Bogert, Julian Pleasant Britz, Lord Charnwood, Lewis Clinton, Frederick Diamond Colson, Edmund Ezra Day, John Charles Lounsberry Fish, Felix Frankfurter, James Picken Harrold, George S. Hellman, Mary (Mrs. Timothy) Hopkins, Oscar Lewis, Robert Harper Murray, Jackson E. Reynolds, Sao-Ke Alfred Sze, Martin Travieso, Joseph Edgar Uihlein, and Frederick Campbell Woodward.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_d93ef72e5e35574d12d49c5fe19a1dfe">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Edwin Hamlin Woodruff papers, #18-1-1703. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
